        "customfield_12310192": "The newly added parameter \"hive.reloadable.aux.jars.path\" is serving for the complement of the previous configuration \"hive.aux.jars.path\". In order to making the HiveServer2 as a service, it should not be restarted when the auxiliary jars changed. In this JIRA, a new command \"reload\" with a parameter \"hive.reloadable.aux.jars.path\" can be used for avoid the scheduling maintenance window for every jar change. User can execute the reload command via the beeline to make the HS2 aware of the changes made in the path specified by the parameter \"hive.reloadable.aux.jars.path\". And the supported changes including adding, removing or updating jar files.",
